{ Inter-obj external declarations for Delphi linker resolution (COFF/x64 only).  }
{ The Win64 COFF linker uses COMDAT sections - each function is in its own       }
{ section, included only when explicitly referenced. Without these declarations,  }
{ cross-obj references remain unresolved (E2065).                                 }
{ Win32 OMF objects (bcc32) include ALL symbols from a linked .obj file, so these }
{ declarations are not needed. Also, dcc32 ignores the 'name' clause of          }
{ "external name" for OMF objects.                                                }
{$IFDEF CPUX64}

